commit_message:
Close #21825: Only lock OpenGL texture cache when using multi-threading (#21952)

Fixes #21825 by making 'DrawingLocks' which lock only if multi threaded drawing is enabled. Refactors TTF.cpp to use this.

Also cleans up some header files, modernises constants, and removes code to avoid using shared_mutex on MacOS builds. This was originally added because older versions of MacOS didn't support this in the STL.

issues.title: Avoid locking the OpenGL TextureCache during single threaded drawing
issues.body:
Profiling showed ~4% of time taken to draw a big zoomed out scene with OpenGL is spent locking and unlocking the texture cache, even when drawing is single threaded. Ideally, there should be no locking in single threaded mode. This is already handled in `TTF.cpp` with `FontLockHelper`.

A PR should apply a similar fix for the the texture cache, ideally refactoring both the texture cache and TTF code to use the same lightweight object.  `gConfigGeneral.MultiThreading` should probably also be made atomic.
